Introduction

Park Gyu-ri better known as Gyuri, is a South Korean singer, actress, voice actor, and radio personality under Big Boss Entertainment. She is the Leader, Lead Vocalist, and Center of the South Korean girl group KARA.

She became a child actress with her first television appearance in the 1995 series Today is a Nice Day, in which she played the girlfriend of Kang Ho Dong's brother.

In 2001, she appeared as the teenage version of Kim Jung Eun's character in the drama series Ladies of the Palace.

In July 2016, she joined Motion Media (now known as Dain Entertainment) to continue her career as an actress. The same year she was cast in the historical drama Jang Yeong-Sil.
